commitResults.messageBody:
The address book is built on the Person object and its attributes.

It is not applicable to the updated product, which is an internship
application tracker.

Renaming Person and its related classes, fields and methods allows for
better clarity and more sensible naming.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Status and its associated tests
commitResults.messageBody:
Status has to be provided when adding a new internship to the tracker.

This requires unnecessary inputs from the user as almost all newly-
added internships will still be in progress.

Let's,
* remove the need to provide a status when adding an internship
* make it such that the status command is the only way to update status
* update the relevant tests to reflect these changes

The order of variables of the Internship class are not the same across
related classes and testcases.

Standardising them will allow for easier formatting and less bug-prone
code.

Let's follow the format below:
* Name
* Position
* Status
* Phone
* Email
* Address
* Tasks
* Tags
* Remarks
Co-authored-by: chantellyu <88767281+chantellyu@users.noreply.github.com>

The application only supports viewing internship applications in full
detail.

This causes each internship application to take up a lot of space in
the list.

Showing the full details only after selecting a particular internship
application allows for the original list to be much more compact, so
users can scroll through it more easily.

Let's only show identifying information (Name, Position, Status) in the
original list and display the full details of a particular internship
after it is selected.

---

The application only supports adding tasks to internship applications.

Users have to delete the application and make new one if they made an
error in adding a task, which wastes a lot of time.

Being able to delete individual tasks enables users to correct these
mistakes more easily and quickly.

Let's add the functionality to delete individual tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add testing for Task commands and parsers
commitResults.messageBody:
SelectCommand, AddTaskCommand, DeleteTaskCommand and their respective
parsers lack unit tests and integration tests.

Adding these tests ensures the implementation remains bug-free and
prevent future changes from affecting the functionality of the
application.

Let's add sufficient test cases to test these classes extensively.

Editing an internship requires the user to input an index of the task
they are editing, even when they cannot see the full details of what
they are editing.

This may cause them to edit the wrong internships since they may not
know what exactly they are overwriting.

Incorporating the SelectCommand to let the user view the details first
before editing prevents such mistakes and makes the code more in line
with the AddTask and DeleteTask commands.

Let's make it necessary to select an internship before editing it and
update the relevant tests to reflect these changes.

Refactor AddressBook into InTrack after addition of StatusCommand
commitResults.messageBody:
The addition of StatusCommand has disrupted the refactoring of
AddressBook into InTrack.

Let's change all mentions of AddressBook to InTrack.

Some terms were not accurately represented, hence they needed to be
changed for more coherent naming.

Let's use InTrack to refer to the application as a whole.

The status currently shows as green no matter the status.

Colour-coding the status label will help to clearly display the
application's progress.

Let's format the status label to change colour depending on the status.

The program only allows searching by name for internships. However,
some users may want to search by position being applied for as well.

Creating a new command to search by position allows users to better
navigate their application list.

Let's,
* create a new command to allow searching by position
* refactor mentions of find command to findn which is for searching by
name

FindNCommand and FindPCommand as classes could be clearer, although
they work well enough as command words.

Let's refactor mentions of FindP and FindN to FindPosition and
FindName respectively for more intuitiveness.

Missing test cases for PositionContainsKeywordsPredicate which may lead
to missing bugs.

Let's add a few test cases for PositionContainsKeywordsPredicate.

commitResults.messageBody:
Not being able to sort the list of internship applications when there
is an entry without tasks lowers the usefulness of the feature as there
may not be upcoming deadlines or interviews scheduled yet.

Let's allow SortTimeCommand to sort the list even when there are
applications with no dates.

Let's replace the try-catch block with a conditional instead.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Remark and RemarkCommand InTrack is built on an Internship object and its attributes, and does not have the Remark field. Let's add a Remark field to allow users to store notes and remarks about their internship applications. Users will not need to use the AddCommand to add remarks to their applications, instead let's add a RemarkCommand that will update the Remark field with the user's input. RemarkCommand is in the format: remark [INDEX] [PREFIX].
Update Developer guide Documentation for RemarkCommand has been added
Currently, InTrack has no way of sorting all Internships by the date and time of their tasks.
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add a sort command to help users sort their internship
applications by the date and time of thier tasks.

`sort a` will sort all internships in an ascending manner, with the
internship with the task with the nearest date and time at the top.

`sort d` will sort all the internships in a descending manner, with
the internship with the task with the furthest date and time at the
top.
